      "desc": "Facilities, general.",
      "narrative": "The facility failed to maintain some of their bird enclosures in good repair. The two enclosures housing red-tailed hawks\nare made of wire with wooden frames. Each enclosure had horizontal and vertical boards that showed signs of rot and\ndecay.\nDeteriorated structural components may compromise the integrity of the enclosure and pose a risk of escape or injury to\nthe animals within.\nHousing facilities for birds must be kept in good repair, protect the birds from injury, and restrict other animals from\nentering that may negatively affect the welfare of the birds within. To be corrected by May 15, 2026.\nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives.\nn"
    }
  ],
  "narrative": "3.150(a) \n   \nFacilities, general. \nThe facility failed to maintain some of their bird enclosures in good repair. The two enclosures housing red-tailed hawks \nare made of wire with wooden frames. Each enclosure had horizontal and vertical boards that showed signs of rot and \ndecay.  \n \nDeteriorated structural components may compromise the integrity of the enclosure and pose a risk of escape or injury to \nthe animals within. \n \nHousing facilities for birds must be kept in good repair, protect the birds from injury, and restrict other animals from \nentering that may negatively affect the welfare of the birds within. To be corrected by May 15, 2026. \n \nThis inspection and exit interview were conducted with facility representatives. \n \n n",
